      • Serialized Fields

        • MAX_NUM_RULES

          int MAX_NUM_RULES
          Constants.

        • startRulelist

          RuleNode startRulelist
          The reference to start of the rule list.

        • dataArray

          short[][] dataArray
          2-D aray to hold input data from data file. Note that within the data array records are numbered from zero, thus record one has index 0 etc.

          First index is row (record or TID) number starting from 0, and second is attribute (column) number starting from zero.

        • conversionArray

          int[][] conversionArray
          2-D array used to renumber columns for input data in terms of frequency of single attributes (reordering will enhance performance for some ARM algorithms).

        • reconversionArray

          short[] reconversionArray
          1-D array used to reconvert input data column numbers to their original numbering where the input data has been ordered to enhance computational efficiency.

        • outputSchema

          java.lang.String[] outputSchema
          1-D array to hold output schema.

        • fileName

          java.lang.String fileName
          Command line argument for data file name.

        • outputFileName

          java.lang.String outputFileName
          Command line argument for output file name.

        • testSetFileName

          java.lang.String testSetFileName
          Command line argument for file name for testset (used in classification where separate test and training set files may be used.

        • numCols

          int numCols
          Command line argument for number of columns (attributes) in input data.

        • numRows

          int numRows
          Command line argument for number of rows in input data.

        • support

          double support
          Command line argument for % support (default = 20%).

        • minSupport

          double minSupport
          Minimum support value in terms of number of rows.

          Set when input data is read and the number of records is known, reset if input data is resized so that only N percent is used.

        • confidence

          double confidence
          Command line argument for % confidence (default = 80%).

        • numOneItemSets

          int numOneItemSets
          The number of one itemsets (singletons).

        • numFrequentSets

          int numFrequentSets
          The number of frequent sets identified during processing.

        • numRules

          int numRules
          The number of rules (ARs, CARs or CRs) that have been generated.

        • numClasses

          Number of classes in input data set (input by the user).

        • numRowsInOutputSchema

    • Class TtreeCanvas extends javax.swing.JPanel implements Serializable

      • Serialized Fields

        • nodeArray

          int[][][] nodeArray
          3-D array, indexes: (1) the index for the node, (2) is the Y node index, (3) is an index into the data --- label (item set number), support, node type).

          Five types of node: (a) no branches, (b) siblimng branch only, (c) child branch only, (d) sibling and child branches, and (e) vertical arc.
